The following are prices paid for
cocoa at the main growing centers in  Ivory Coast  from Feb. 26 to
March 4, according to the figures published on the website of
the Bourse du Cafe et du Cacao.  The national average paid was 685  CFA francs  ($1.35) per
kilogram (2.2 pounds), and varied from 700 francs to 650 francs,
the state-run bourse said.  The West African nation, the worldâ€™s biggest cocoa
producer, set the indicative farmgate cocoa price for the
2011-12 season at 1,000 francs on Oct. 3. Prices are in CFA
francs per kilogram ($1 = 504.5 CFA francs).  To contact the reporter on this story:
